body: This adds the option to use a Dart entrypoint instead of a bazel target. There are cases where the bazel build process will fail with error messages in the console (e.g. when the project has not been set up to indicate what the associated targets are or if an entrypoint is linked to multiple targets). The error messages currently point to relevant documentation but we may be able to make project-specific suggestions with later (internal) changes. Another next step is to allow for adding Dart entrypoints to saved configuration files that we can use to generate equivalent VSCode configuration files.

comment_data.body: nit:  make this just `getTarget()` with a comment that it is either a bazel or dart target.
